 </div>
 <div class="space-y-4">
  <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
  <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is the MOQ for wireless car charger OEM?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
  <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">MOQ starts at <strong>500 units</strong> for standard ODM models with custom logo. Full OEM with private tooling: <strong>2,000 units</strong>. Sample turnaround: 3-7 days for standard models, 10-15 days for custom logo samples. Flexible MOQ options available for startup brands and market testing.</p>
  </details>
  <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
  <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What makes TEC cooling important in a car wireless charger mount?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
  <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Car interiors can reach over <strong>50°C (122°F)</strong> in summer. iPhone Qi2/MagSafe throttles charging speed at ambient temperatures above 35°C, capping at 80% battery to protect the device. TEC (Thermoelectric Cooling) semiconductor technology in WOW41 actively cools the charging surface — the only B2B OEM car mount with this technology — maintaining <strong>25W full-speed charging</strong> even in hot vehicles. Combined with a silent turbo fan and large-area heatsink for dual device-and-battery cooling.</p>
  </details>
  <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
  <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Do WOWOHCOOL car mounts support both iPhone and Android?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
  <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes. All WOWOHCOOL car mounts use Qi2 universal wireless charging standard compatible with <strong>iPhone 12-17 (15W/25W MagSafe)</strong> and <strong>Android Qi2 devices</strong> (Samsung Galaxy S25, Pixel 10, etc.). For non-MagSafe Android phones, the WOW35 electric clamp model provides universal grip without magnets. Android users can add a magnetic ring case for compatibility with magnetic models WOW39, WOW41, and WOW19S.</p>
  </details>
  <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
  <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Do your car mounts work with thick phone cases?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
  <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes. Our N52H neodymium magnets are the strongest commercial grade available — with up to <strong>1400g suction force</strong> on WOW19S. They maintain secure magnetic hold through most protective cases up to 3mm thickness. For very thick rugged cases (4mm+), we recommend magnetic-compatible cases or our magnetic ring accessories. WOW35 electric clamp model works with <strong>any phone regardless of case thickness</strong> — no magnets needed.</p>
  </details>
  <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
  <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Can I get E-Mark certification for car wireless charger mounts?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
  <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">E-Mark (ECE R10) is required for automotive electronics sold in the EU aftermarket. While wireless chargers powered via USB-C from the cigarette lighter port occupy a regulatory gray area, WOWOHCOOL can provide <strong>E-Mark-ready designs</strong> with proper EMI shielding and automotive-grade components. We recommend E-Mark certification for brands selling to automotive retailers and EU distributors. Full certification documentation and testing support included with OEM orders.</p>
  </details>
  <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
  <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What ventilation mounts are included?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
  <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">All models include a universal vent clip mount with anti-sway clamp. WOW28 includes a suction-cup base for dashboard/windshield mounting. <strong>Custom mount options</strong> (CD slot, cup holder, adhesive dash, Tesla-specific, 17mm ball joint) available for OEM orders. MOQ 500 for custom mount type bundling.</p>
  </details>
  <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
  <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">How long does OEM/ODM car mount production take?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
  <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">OEM (standard models with custom logo): <strong>25-30 days</strong> after sample approval. ODM (custom enclosure or mechanism design): <strong>45-60 days</strong> including tooling. Both timelines include 4-stage QC (IQC → IPQC → FQC → OQC) with 4-hour 100% aging test. Express air freight: 5-7 days to EU/US. Seafreight: 25-35 days.</p>
  </details>
  <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
  <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is a supercapacitor car phone mount and how is it different?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
  <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">The WOW35 electric clamp car mount uses a <strong>supercapacitor</strong> instead of a traditional battery for power-off operation. After the engine is turned off, the supercapacitor provides enough stored energy for up to two full open/close cycles — unlike battery-powered clamps that degrade over time. Supercapacitors offer <strong>500,000+ charge cycles</strong> (vs ~500 for lithium batteries) and maintain consistent performance from -20°C to 70°C. This is the only B2B OEM car mount with this technology.</p>
  </details>
